<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New Teacher for the Class: British comedian Billy Connolly will be the new head 
of the class in the ABC series "Head of the Class." 
</P>
<P>
Warner Bros. Television, the show's producer, announced Tuesday that Connolly 
will star as the history teacher as the show goes into production Aug. 2 for 
the fall season. Connolly plays an exchange teacher from Scotland as he 
replaces the Charlie Moore character played by Howard Hesseman in the class for 
gifted students. The series also stars Robin Givens, Khrystyne Haje and others. 
BETH KLEID 
