<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BRADLEY APPOINTS 21 TO CITY COMMISSIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mayor Tom Bradley announced a major shake-up Tuesday in the commissions that 
help shape Los Angeles city policy, naming 21 newcomers to head the 
commissions, including the spouses of two top aides. 
</P>
<P>
Despite the personal relationship of two appointees to his aides, the mayor 
said the appointments reflected a broad cross-section of the city's population. 
</P>
<P>
One appointee is Harry Usher, the No. 2 man in the Los Angeles Olympic 
Organizing Committee, who was named to the Cultural Affairs panel. Usher, who 
also was president of the U.S. Football League, is married to Bradley's legal 
counsel, Jane Ellison. Julie Depoian, who is married to Bradley aide Phil 
Depoian, was named to the Civil Service Commission, Bradley's press secretary 
Bill Chandler said. 
</P>
<P>
Also, William Robertson, executive secretary for the county Federation of 
Labor, was named to the Recreation and Parks Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
