<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MEXICAN FRUIT FLY FOUND; NO SPRAYING 
PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
State agriculture officials announced Tuesday the discovery of a Mexican fruit 
fly in Watts about a quarter of a mile from a Compton neighborhood already 
infested with the pest. The immature male was trapped Monday in a lemon tree. 
Eradication officials said the discovery will be treated with the release of 
sterile Mexflies and will not require aerial malathion spraying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
