<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wynn's International Inc.: The Fullerton diversified company reported 
second-quarter net income of $1.6 million, a slight drop from the $1.7 million 
posted for the year-earlier period. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue fell 3%, to $68.5 million from $70.5 million. The company attributed 
the lower revenue to sluggish sales at its automotive air-conditioning 
subsidiary. Net income for the first six months fell 33% to $3.3 million, down 
from $4.9 million a year earlier. Sales declined 2%, to $141.1 million from 
$143.6 million. Wynn's is a supplier of auto air conditioners, O-rings, seals, 
molded rubber products, petrochemical specialty products and builder hardware. 
</P>
</TEXT>
