<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nestle Selling Stouffer Unit: Nestle Enterprises Inc. put up for sale its 65 
restaurants operated by subsidiary Stouffer Restaurant Co. 
</P>
<P>
Nestle said it decided not to expand its restaurant business and instead would 
prepare the division for sale as part of a long-range business strategy. 
Stouffer's, which has been in the restaurant business for 66 years, operates 
"Top-of" restaurants -- atop high-rise buildings -- in New York, Cleveland, 
Boston, Pittsburgh, Philadelphia and Columbus, Ohio. The company also operates 
restaurants in several cities under the names J. B. Winberie, James Tavern, 
Rusty Scupper and Parkers' Lighthouse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
