</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Dynamics Corp. announced special assignments for several senior 
executives to provide management focus on the Navy's A-12 advanced tactical 
aircraft program at its Ft. 
</P>
<P>
Worth division. Herbert F. Rogers, president and chief operating officer, will 
relocate from St. Louis to Ft. Worth and assume the duties of general manager 
of that division. Charles A. Anderson, corporate vice president and general 
manager of the Ft. Worth division, will direct the A-12 program. John A. 
Lamers, vice president of the A-12 program, will become deputy program 
director. William A. Anders, General Dynamics vice chairman, will assume 
Rogers' corporate management responsibilities. 
</P>
