<HEADLINE>
<P>
RIGHTS GROUP SAYS ISRAELI RULES FUEL SLAYING OF ARABS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A U.S. human rights group charged today that Israeli army regulations encourage 
soldiers to open fire on Palestinians in the occupied territories with little 
fear of being punished. 
</P>
<P>
In a report titled "The Israeli Army and the Intifada: Policies that Contribute 
to the Killings," the New York-based Middle East Watch accused the military of 
failing to adequately investigate deaths caused by army gunfire and prosecute 
soldiers suspected of abuses. 
</P>
<P>
The report's conclusions were similar to those of the Israeli human rights 
group B'Tselem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
