<P>
MISSING CADDIE COSTS GOLFER HIS SHOT AT A RECORD ROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FARMINGDALE, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A misplaced caddie cost Doug Miller a two-stroke penalty and a course record. 
</P>
<P>
Miller, a 28-year-old assistant pro from East Norwich, N.Y., shot a 5-under-par 
66 to take the lead in the partially completed first round of the New York 
State Open on Tuesday, but it should have been a course-record 64 on the 
difficult Bethpage State Park's Black course. 
</P>
<P>
He was penalized when he was unable to restart on time after a three-hour 
morning rain delay because his caddie didn't show up on the third hole with his 
clubs. 
</P>
<P>
"He was waiting inside for me," Miller said. "We crossed signals a bit. It's my 
fault. It's the player's responsibility." 
</P>
