<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
COLTS SIGN KICKER MAX ZENDEJAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANDERSON, Ind. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Indianapolis Colts, guarding against the possibility of a contract holdout 
by veteran Dean Biasucci, have signed place-kicker Max Zendejas. 
</P>
<P>
Biasucci, fifth in Colts' career scoring with 391 points in five seasons, is 
one of the team's eight unsigned veterans. He is not expected to be in camp 
when the veterans report to the Anderson University training facility on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Zendejas, whose brief NFL career includes previous stops in Washington and 
Green Bay, signed a two-year contract Tuesday and said he regards it as a good 
opportunity to get back into football. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm just here for myself and to see if I can get in and help this team in any 
way this year," Zendejas said. 
</P>
